Mongo-docker is a docker-based framework for testing complicated setups

All you need is the mdocker module and some luck.

Follow the steps in the INSTALL file, import the mdocker module, create a new 

Some useful commands:
1. Build a new image named mongodb_1
	docker build -t alex/mongodb_1 .
2. Stop and remove all existing containers:
	docker stop $(docker ps -a -q) && docker rm $(docker ps -a -q)
